## Prerequisites
1. Be connected to the F5 VPN and login in via the UI as a admin not SSO session 
2. Check if the certificate has expired by navigating to `Palo` > Select Device > Setup > Management and under the header "Device Certificate".When the "Current Device Certificate Status" states valid then no further action required if it states expired proceed to renew.
3. To do the renewal you will need to teh Palo Cutomer Support Portal, you will need to have an account setup for this. If you do not have an account please ask on the PlatformOperations channel on slack, for a current user to assist you.
4. Ensure you have the device serial number for the device you are updating the certificate for before proceeding.

## Updating the Palo Device Certificate

1. Login into the Palo Customer Support Portal
2. Click on "Products" in left menu panel > Select "Device Certificates" 
3  From dropdown click "Generate OTP" button > select either for Next-Gen Firewall or Panorama > select the relevant device serial number obtained from step 4 in Prerequisites.
4. Copy the OTP code provided as it this required for the next step.
5. Navigate to the Palo Alto Device in the UI; Select Device > Setup > Management and click "Get Certificate" and paste the OTP code from step 4.
6. Refresh the UI and ensure the certificate status is now valid.
